    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the different views but it feels like you're just saying \"it depends\" to avoid the question. some people say that treating healthcare as a market commodity instead of a right is fundamentally unethical. don't you think there's a moral weight to the \"human right\" side that makes it more of a fact than just an opinion?",
